# CLAUDE.md - Consumer App Example (Fitness)

> This is a filled-in example showing what CLAUDE.md looks like for a consumer mobile app.
> Copy the blank template from CLAUDE.md.example and adapt it to your product.

## Shipwright Auto-Start

When a new Claude Code session begins, run `/start` to launch the Shipwright orchestrator.

## Product

- **Name:** TrailSync
- **Category:** Consumer fitness app for trail runners and hikers
- **Stage:** MVP (pre-revenue, 12K MAU from beta, seed-funded)
- **Target users:** Recreational trail runners (25-45) who run 2-4 times per week on trails and want route planning, safety features, and community
- **Core job-to-be-done:** Help trail runners find, plan, and safely complete runs on new trails without needing to research conditions, navigation, and safety separately

## Key Metrics

| Metric | Current Value | Target | Timeframe |
|---|---|---|---|
| North Star: Runs completed per week (all users) | 3,200 | 10,000 | Q4 2026 |
| WAU / MAU ratio | 0.31 | 0.45 | Q3 2026 |
| D7 retention | 28% | 40% | Q3 2026 |
| Runs with safety check-in enabled | 41% | 60% | Q4 2026 |

## Strategic Priorities (Current Quarter)

1. **Retention loop:** Build post-run summary sharing (route map, elevation, photos) to create a social loop that brings users back.
2. **Trail condition reports:** Let users tag trail conditions (muddy, icy, downed tree) during or after runs. This is the #1 feature request and our differentiator over AllTrails.
3. **Onboarding redesign:** Current onboarding drops 55% of users before first run. Reduce to 35%.

## What We're NOT Doing

- Monetization. Too early. We need retention before we deserve revenue.
- Road running features. Strava owns that. We're trails only.
- Hardware integrations beyond Apple Watch and Garmin. No bandwidth for Fitbit, Whoop, etc. yet.

## Personas

### Weekend Warrior Jess
- **Role:** Runs trails 2-3x per week, mostly on weekends. Not competitive, just enjoys being outdoors.
- **Goals:** Find new trails near her that match her fitness level. Know what to expect before she goes (distance, elevation, current conditions). Share her runs with friends.
- **Pain points:** AllTrails reviews are outdated. She's gotten lost twice using poorly marked routes. She runs alone and her partner worries.

### Trail Community Carlos
- **Role:** Experienced trail runner, runs 4-5x per week, active in local running groups.
- **Goals:** Contribute to the trail community, find running partners, discover challenging new routes.
- **Pain points:** Scattered info across Facebook groups, Strava, and AllTrails. No single place to see what conditions are like right now.

## Competitors

| Competitor | Type | Our Advantage | Their Advantage |
|---|---|---|---|
| AllTrails | Direct | Real-time trail conditions, safety check-in, better social | Massive trail database, brand awareness, paid subscriber base |
| Strava | Indirect | Trail-specific features, route planning with conditions | Social network effects, road + trail, deep fitness analytics |
| onX Backcountry | Indirect | Simpler UX, community focus, running-specific | Offline maps, hunting/camping audience, topo detail |

## Conventions

- **User stories:** "As a [persona], I want [action] so that [outcome]"
- **PRD format:** Working Backwards
- **Prioritization:** ICE scoring (we move fast, RICE is overkill at this stage)
- **Roadmap style:** Now / Next / Later, reviewed biweekly
- **Sprint cadence:** 1-week sprints
- **Definition of Done:** Shipped to TestFlight/Play Store beta, core flows tested manually, analytics events firing

## Tools & Integrations

- **Project management:** Linear
- **Documentation:** Notion
- **Analytics:** PostHog (self-hosted) + Firebase for crash reporting
- **Communication:** Discord (team + community)
- **Design:** Figma

## Glossary

| Term | Definition |
|---|---|
| Run | A completed trail activity (started and finished, not abandoned) |
| Safety check-in | Feature that sends GPS location to emergency contact at intervals during a run |
| Trail condition | User-submitted tag about current trail state (muddy, icy, clear, etc.) |
| WAU | Weekly active users |
| D7 | 7-day retention (% of new users who return within 7 days) |
